----

This product bundles or depends on the following third-party components,
which are available under their respective licenses. Complete SBOMs are
produced by `deploy/sbom/generate.sh`; a summary follows.

Gateway (Go, stdlib-only) - no third-party runtime dependencies.

Control API (Python):
  * FastAPI (MIT)                     https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi
  * Uvicorn (BSD-3-Clause)            https://github.com/encode/uvicorn
  * SQLAlchemy (MIT)                  https://github.com/sqlalchemy/sqlalchemy
  * Alembic (MIT)                     https://github.com/sqlalchemy/alembic
  * Pydantic (MIT)                    https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic
  * psycopg (LGPL-3.0)                https://github.com/psycopg/psycopg
  * cryptography (Apache-2.0 / BSD)   https://github.com/pyca/cryptography
  * jsonschema (MIT)                  https://github.com/python-jsonschema/jsonschema
  * PyJWT (MIT)                       https://github.com/jpadilla/pyjwt
  * httpx (BSD-3-Clause)              https://github.com/encode/httpx

Detectors (Python):
  * regex (Apache-2.0)                https://github.com/mrabarnett/mrab-regex
  * PyYAML (MIT)                      https://github.com/yaml/pyyaml

Automation:
  * APScheduler (MIT)                 https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler
  * PyPDF2 (BSD-3-Clause)             https://github.com/py-pdf/pypdf

Console (TypeScript):
  * React (MIT)                       https://github.com/facebook/react
  * React Router (MIT)                https://github.com/remix-run/react-router
  * @supabase/supabase-js (MIT)       https://github.com/supabase/supabase-js
  * Vite (MIT)                        https://github.com/vitejs/vite

Vendored data:
  * `gateway/internal/detector/secrets/rules.json` — patterns compatible with
     Gitleaks (MIT); see https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks for the upstream
     ruleset. Patterns are re-authored, not directly copied; if any pattern
     is byte-identical it remains covered by the upstream MIT license.

Third-party services (optional, not bundled):
  * Together.ai, DeepInfra, OpenAI, Groq, Ollama, vLLM - operator-selected
     backends for the LLM Judge. Configured via `config/providers.yaml`.
     Each is governed by its own terms of service.
